pwnsjp (0.9.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add missing #include.
  * Use tiparm() instead of tparm(). (API of the former is more reliable.)
  * Refurbish README.
  * Refurbish the --help message.
  * Improve the manual page:
    + Rephrase descriptions of --help, --version.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Add check against BSD make. (Only GNU make is supported.)
    + Filter out feature test macros from ncurses CFLAGS.
      https://bugs.debian.org/900987
    + Drop support for (deprecated) LOADLIBES.
    + Stop using macros from autoconf-archive.
    + Teach the configure script about the issue tracker.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Mon, 29 Jan 2024 20:50:38 +0100

pwnsjp (0.9) unstable; urgency=low

  * Get rid of the “pwnsjpi” binary.
    + Make “pwnsjp” without arguments run the text UI.
    + Add the -a/--all option to print all entries.
  * Make the command-line argument parser stricter.
  * Make --help print to stdout, not stderr.
  * Make --version print to stdout, not stderr.
  * Simplify the --version message.
  * Make --version print also ncurses version.
  * Drop support for ISO-8859-16 encoding.
  * Fix typo in ASCII transliteration of Σ (Greek capital letter sigma).
  * Improve the build system:
    + Install the manpage to the correct directory.
    + Install the manpage with the correct permissions.
    + Don't use non-portable options for install(1).
    + Don't use non-portable constructs for sed(1).
    + Disable network access for xsltproc.
    + Check for the DocBook stylesheet availability at configure time.
    + Rewrite encoding helper scripts so that they don't require glibc data
      files.
    + Drop support for konwert(1).
      (This codepath has never worked correctly.)
    + Don't hardcode Perl path in shebangs.
    + Improve error handling.
  * Improve the manual pages:
    + Improve wording.
    + Use the YYYY-MM-DD date format.
  * Fix typos in the documentation.
  * Update the Unshield homepage URL.
  * Update the requirements list in README.
  * Put license into a separate file.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Thu, 14 Sep 2017 21:30:45 +0200

pwnsjp (0.8.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Update versions and dates in README, TODO, and in the configure script.
  * Fix a few type mismatches on 64-bit architectures.
  * Don't require non-standard <endian.h> and <byteswap.h> headers.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Use pkg-config to determine ncursesw location.
    + Fall back to default compiler flags if pkg-config data for zlib or
      ncursesw cannot be found.
    + Strip trailing slash from the --with-dictdir argument.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Wed, 12 Jun 2013 16:48:21 +0200

pwnsjp (0.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * Change version numbering scheme.
  * Fix incorrect rendering of quotation marks.
  * Rephrase some error messages.
  * Remove the “AUTHOR” section from the manual pages, as per man-pages(7)
    recommendation.
  * Fix “make distclean” to remove also files generated by make, not only
    those generated by configure.
  * Drop Intel C++ Compiler compatibility code.

